<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>How It Works | ShikshaNet</title>
 <style>
    @import url("https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Geist:wght@400;600&display=swap");

* {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

body {
  background-color: #ffffff;
  color: #000000;
  font-family: "Geist", sans-serif;
  line-height: 1.6;
}

header {
  text-align: center;
  padding: 60px 20px 40px;
  border-bottom: 2px solid black;
}

header h1 {
  font-size: 2.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
  letter-spacing: 1px;
}

header p {
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  color: #444;
}

.workflow {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 40px;
  padding: 60px 12%;
}

.step {
  border: 2px solid black;
  border-radius: 20px;
  padding: 30px;
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
  background-color: #fff;
}

.step:hover {
  background-color: #000;
  color: #fff;
  transform: translateY(-5px);
}

.step h2 {
  font-size: 1.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 15px;
}

footer {
  text-align: center;
  padding: 30px;
  border-top: 2px solid black;
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: #444;
}
    </style>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <h1>How ShikshaNet Works</h1>
    <p>Connecting teachers and students through a smart, seamless learning experience.</p>
  </header>

  <section class="workflow">
    <div class="step">
      <h2>1. Teacher Uploads Material</h2>
      <p>Teachers log into the platform and upload assignments, tutorials, experiments, and study materials. These can be shared with an entire class or individual students.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <h2>2. Students Access Dashboard</h2>
      <p>Students log into their personalized dashboard to view assigned work, access tutorials and notes, and track their learning progress.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <h2>3. Assignment Submission</h2>
      <p>Students complete and submit their assignments directly through the platform with integrated file upload and text input options.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <h2>4. Review & Feedback</h2>
      <p>Teachers review submitted assignments, provide constructive feedback, and assign grades, helping students understand their performance better.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <h2>5. Progress Tracking</h2>
      <p>The platform updates each student’s statistics—showing completion rates, attendance, and academic performance on a visual dashboard.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <h2>6. Notifications & Updates</h2>
      <p>Automatic notifications keep both teachers and students informed about new assignments, upcoming deadlines, grades, and important announcements in real-time.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer>
    <p>© 2025 ShikshaNet — Empowering Digital Learning</p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>